---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const effectiveDate = 'July 13, 2026';
const basePath = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.endsWith('/')
  ? import.meta.env.BASE_URL
  : `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`;
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy" description="SPRITEbot privacy policy.">
  <section class="page-hero legal-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Privacy Policy</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Effective {effectiveDate}</p>
  </section>

  <div class="legal-content">
    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains what data SPRITEbot ("the Bot") collects, how it is used,
        and how you can manage or delete it. By using the Bot, you agree to the practices
        described here.
      </p>
      <p>
        SPRITEbot operates on the Discord platform. This policy covers data handled by the Bot
        itself. For information about how Discord handles your data, see the
        <a href="https://discord.com/privacy">Discord Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Data We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        SPRITEbot collects and stores only the data necessary to provide its features. This
        includes:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Discord identifiers:</strong> User IDs, server (guild) IDs, channel IDs, role
          IDs, and message IDs used to connect commands and features to the correct context.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Game and campaign data:</strong> Game names, descriptions, stat templates,
          character sheets, inventory items, and other configuration created through bot commands.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Roleplay content:</strong> In-character and out-of-character message text
          submitted through <code>/ic</code> and <code>/ooc</code> commands, along with webhook
          message references used for editing and deletion.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Thread bump configuration:</strong> Channel and thread references and scheduling
          preferences for automatic thread bumping.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Transcription data:</strong> When a GM explicitly starts a voice transcription
          session, the Bot stores session metadata and generated transcript files.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Subscription status:</strong> Discord subscription identifiers used to
          determine whether a server has Premium access. We do not store payment details.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not collect message content from general server chat. The Bot only processes
        content explicitly submitted through its commands and interactions.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>How We Use Your Data</h2>
      <p>Collected data is used solely to operate SPRITEbot's features:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Running campaigns, managing characters, and processing game commands</li>
        <li>Proxying in-character roleplay messages via webhooks</li>
        <li>Tracking inventory and character stats</li>
        <li>Scheduling and executing thread bumps</li>
        <li>Producing GM-requested voice transcription output</li>
        <li>Determining subscription and feature access</li>
        <li>Diagnosing errors and improving Bot reliability</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>What We Don't Do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We do not sell, rent, or share your data with third parties.</li>
        <li>We do not use your data for advertising, profiling, or behavioral targeting.</li>
        <li>We do not disclose data to data brokers, ad networks, or monetization services.</li>
        <li>We do not use message content or API data to train machine learning or AI models.</li>
        <li>We do not mine or scrape Discord data beyond what is needed for Bot functionality.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        We do not share your data with third parties except in the following circumstances:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>When required by law, legal process, or government request</li>
        <li>When you explicitly direct us to share data (for example, posting a character sheet to a channel)</li>
        <li>With service providers who help us operate the Bot, bound by confidentiality obligations</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
      <p>
        Data is retained only as long as necessary to provide the Bot's features. When data is
        no longer needed, it is deleted.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Deleted game and character data may be held during a soft-delete recovery window before
          permanent removal.
        </li>
        <li>
          Transcripts are posted into the configured Discord text channel when a GM stops
          transcription. Server admins manage those files per their own server policies.
        </li>
        <li>
          When the Bot is removed from a server or a subscription ends, associated data will be
          deleted after a reasonable retention period.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You can request deletion of your data at any time. See the Contact section below for how
        to reach us. We will process deletion requests promptly in accordance with Discord's
        Developer Policy and applicable privacy laws.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on your location, you may have rights under privacy laws such as the GDPR,
        UK GDPR, CCPA/CPRA, or LGPD. These may include the right to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access the personal data we hold about you</li>
        <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
        <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
        <li>Object to or restrict certain processing</li>
        <li>Receive your data in a portable format</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, contact us using the methods listed in the Contact
        section. We will respond within the timeframes required by applicable law.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Security</h2>
      <p>
        We use commercially reasonable measures to protect your data, including encryption at
        rest and access controls. However, no system is perfectly secure. If we become aware of
        unauthorized access to your data, we will notify affected users and Discord as required
        by applicable law.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        SPRITEbot is not directed at children under 13 (or the minimum age required in your
        jurisdiction). We do not knowingly collect data from users below this age. If we learn
        that we have collected data from a child under the applicable minimum age, we will
        delete it promptly.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically. Material changes will be communicated
        through the Bot's support channels or website. Continued use of the Bot after changes
        are posted constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        To request data deletion, ask questions about this policy, or exercise your privacy
        rights, contact the SPRITEbot maintainer through
        the <a href="https://discord.gg/eXktxzKxze">support server</a> or the
        contact channels linked from the Bot.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
